{"key":"processedPost-7768963","value":{"id":7768963,"first":7767352,"last":7774029,"when":1197914687,"utime":"12/17/07 08:04 PM","content":"The purpose of the 'roll' in dunk and roll is so that vermiculite will stick to the wet cake. Vermiculite absorbs water and therefore acts as a moisture reservoir.  You can mist the verm on the cake and it will slowly release that absorbed water to the mycelium.<br /><br />Perlite does not absorb water.  Perlite is crystalline and is about as absorbant as window glass.  Putting perlite on your cakes will not serve as a moisture reservoir or anything else.<br /><br />Read here: <a href=\"/forums/showflat.php/Number/6610766#Post6610766\" class=\"pp\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.shroomery.org/forums/<wbr>showflat.php/Number/6610766#Post6<wbr>610766</a><br />RR","title":"Re: dunk and roll, can you roll in perlite if you out of verm"}}